Title: 'From No where to Portugal '
DateModified: '2019-03-04'
DatePublished: '2019-03-04'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/from-no-where-to-portugal
SetInCountry: South Africa
Category: A leap into the unknown
AuthorName: Light Raseasala
AuthorCountry: South Africa
Text: 'English, Spanish, French and Portuguese what does this languages have in common.
  They are the most spoken languages in the world. This article will cover some aspects
  of the mighty Portugal.


  If you ask a football fan about Portugal they will tell you about Christiano Ronaldo,but
  besides that what else does Portugal has to offer. For start Portugal which is officially
  known as the Portuguese Rupublic is located on the Iberian Peninsula in the southwestern
  Europe. It is boarded by Spain in the  eastern and Atlantic Ocean on the west and
  South.


  The official language of Portugal is Portuguese with Mirandese as the recognized
  language. 93% are recognized Portuguese ethnic. The capital city of Portugal Lisbon,
  with Porto as being the second largest city on Portugal.


  Portugal is blessed with beautiful natural landmarks as it known as the best outdoor
  destination in Europe. The country is one of the oldest civilization in Europe and
  the capital Lisbon is the second  oldest capital in Europe after Athens. Portugal
  is cheaper as compare to the neighboring countries.


  Portugal is a rich country with ancient history. They  continue making history when
  it comes to sport. Football (soccer) is the most popular sports, where the national
  team has just recently won Euro cup. Ronaldo is the treasure of the country where
  international airport is named after him.


  If you love outdoor, and your on tide budget definitely Portugal is your destination.
  Portugal has one of the friendly people with less cases of racism.'
